Michael Rocchi <mrocchi@awninsurance.ca>
​Specialty Risk Claims <Specialty.RiskClaims@nbfc.com>
​Wayne Cheng <Wayne.Cheng@nbfc.com>;
​Sean Terkildsen
​Good afternoon,
We’ve received a request for reconsideration on this claim.  This is one of the first files adjusted with the impact of a comparison of the CBB value at time of loss compared to insurer payout.
The CBB value used in the calculation resulted in a reduction in the GAP payout of almost $6,000.
In reviewing the specifics of the claim, we find we are dealing with a new vehicle that accumulated less than 2,500 km in one month before it was written off.
The insurer settlement was more than the MSRP stated on the bill of sale, but came up short on compensation allowed for the aftermarket accessories.
The insurer settlement was based on a valuation report that relied on selling prices of three vehicles of the same year, trim level, and with modest adjustments for mileage.
In this case we feel we should have relied on the insurer’s valuation as it is apparent that the CBB values overstated the vehicle retail value, when compared to the actual vehicle samples contained in the valuation report.
Consequently, we support a reconsideration on this settlement amount for this claim.
A revised worksheet outlining the additional $5,989.17 payable.  The bill of sale, valuation report and CBB report are also enclosed for ease of reference.
We appreciate your time in considering this revision to the  GAP claim settlement.
Please let us know if any additional information is required.
Thank you,
Michael
